		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName> <date>18<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Sept&#47;62</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Your esteemed letter came<lb/> to hand in due course&#44; and their several in<lb/>closures were delivered.  The Books were like<lb/>wise received&#44; and I have disposed of a few<lb/> of them.  I felt sorry to learn by your last<lb/> of your indisposition&#44; and trust that your<lb/> health has since been quite restored.  I am<lb/> interested in the article on Education in the<lb/> Occident.  Here things fluctuate much&#44; I<lb/> regret to say.  The succeeding numbers of the<lb/> Occident for <persName>Mr. Myers</persName> you will please for<lb/>ward to <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>.  <persName>Mr. David</persName> having left<lb/> that <placeName>Island</placeName> some time since for <placeName>Sydney</placeName>.<lb/>  <persName>Mr. M.</persName> was offered the situation of Minister<lb/> of the German congregation there&#44; a much</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>better one than he enjoyed here&#44; and he therefore<lb/> left our shores on <date>Tuesday</date> night.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">It does indeed appear as if nothing but the<lb/> war is now thought of in <placeName>America</placeName>&#58; still I<lb/> think it is natural&#44; and the world looks on<lb/> anxiously at the contest now waging.  Here<lb/> there is nothing of interest to dilate upon&#59; and<lb/> without even the change of seasons to mark<lb/> the progress of time&#44; each year seems to pass<lb/> away unperceived&#44; but for the trials which<lb/> beset every life.  The New Year and ensuing<lb/> holy days are again fast approaching&#44; and<lb/> I therefore conclude this with friendly greet<lb/>ings thereon.  That our Heavenly Father may<lb/> inscribe you to a happy life is the earnest<lb/> hope of&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Rev. Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(12)"><persName role="author">D. M. Pizal</persName></p>
			
